Di '''Ba'ai Fiet''' (nastaliq بهائیت fa ''Bahá'iyyat'', Arabik بهائية ''Bahá'iyya'' IPAc-en bəˈhaɪ, Ingglish, "Bahá'í" IPAc-en bəˈhaɪ pronongx wid tuu silibl askaadn tu di [http://news.bahai.org/media-information/style-guide/ pronunciation guide] pah di Bahá'í World News Service Website (Bahá'í: ''Ba-HIGH''). Ina Poerjan, بهائی IPA-fa bæhɒːʔiː pronongx wid chrii silibl. Di egzak riilizieshan a di Ingglish pronongxieshan vieri. Di [[Axfad Ingglish Dikshineri|Axfad Ingglish Dikshineri]] ab IPAc-en bæˈhɑːiː riispel ba HAH ee, Merriam-Webster ab IPAc-en bɑːˈhɑːiː riispe l bah HAH ee, ah di Random House Dictionary ab IPAc-en bəˈhɑːiː riispel bə HAH ee, aal wid chrii silibl. Si Bahá’i Study [https://archive.org/details/ABahaiGlossaryAndPronunciationGuide/ A Baha'i Glossary and Pronunciation Guide], Amin Banani, MP3 ah [http://bahai-l rary.com/wttp/programs.html/ A Guide to Pronunciation part 1 and 2] Darius Shahrokh, Windows to the Past Series, Bahá’i Library&nbsp;– , fi muo pronongxieshan inschrokshan.) a [[Monotiyizim|monotiyistik]] rilijan we emfasaiz di pirichual yuuniti a aal [[Yumankain|yuumankain]]. Chrii kuor prinsipl extablish di biesis fi Ba'ai tiichin ah dakchrin: di yuuniti a Gad, dat a onggl wan [[Gad|Gad]] uu a di suos a aal [[Krieshan mit|krieshan]]; di yuuniti a rilijan, dat aal mieja rilijan ab di siem pirichual suos ah kom frah di sieh Gad; ah di yuuniti a yuumaniti, dat aal yuuman eh-kriet iikual, kopl wid yuuniti ina daivoersiti, dat daivoersiti a ries ah kolcha wot aprishieshan ah axeptans.<ref>Hutter, Manfred, ''Encyclopedia of Religion'', ed. Lindsay Jones, 2nd edition, Vol.2, 2005, Macmillan Reference, Detroit, Michigan, ISBN 0-02-865733-0, pp. 737–740</ref> Askaadn tu di Ba'ai Fiet tiichin, di yuuman poerpos a fi laan fi nuo ah fi lob Gad chuu soch metad az [[Praya|praya]], [[Inchrospekshan|riflekshan]] ah fi bi a saabis tu yuumaniti.

